      {q:"The Maldives held an underwater cabinet meeting in 2009 — what was the purpose?", ch:["To draw global attention to climate change and rising sea levels threatening to submerge the islands — ministers signed a document in diving gear","To celebrate the discovery of an underwater archaeological site","To protest a UN decision about territorial waters","To launch a new underwater tourism initiative"], a:0, cat:"🌊 Culture"},
      {q:"What is the capital city of the Maldives, and what makes it unusual?", ch:["Malé — one of the world's most densely populated cities, crammed onto an island of just 5.8 square kilometres with over 150,000 people","Addu City — built on a coral atoll far from the other islands","Fuvahmulah — the only single-island atoll in the Maldives","Hulhumalé — a purpose-built artificial island near the capital"], a:0, cat:"🗺️ Geography"}
